H0.text: Which US state lends its name to a baked pudding, made with ice cream, sponge and meringue. US-AL

H1.text: Which US state lends its name to a baked pudding, made with ice cream, sponge and meringue. US-CA

H2.text: Which US state lends its name to a baked pudding, made with ice cream, sponge and meringue. US-FL

H3.text: Which US state lends its name to a baked pudding, made with ice cream, sponge and meringue. US-AK

A4.text: Baked Alaska, also known as Bombe Alaska, omelette norvégienne, omelette surprise, or omelette sibérienne depending on the country, is a dessert consisting of ice cream and cake topped with browned meringue.

A5.text: The name 'baked Alaska' was supposedly coined in 1876 at Delmonico's, a restaurant in New York City, to honor the acquisition by the United States of Alaska from the Russian Empire in March 1867.
